The paper deals with algorithms for sampling edges from a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of queries to access the graph suggests that the paper may belong to the data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM) categories. The focus on uniform sampling and the analysis of the number of queries required suggests that the paper may also belong to the game theory (cs.GT) or information theory (cs.IT) categories. Finally, the use of neighbor queries suggests that the paper may also belong to the social and information networks (cs.SI) category.
